## Firmware binary exception

Peak-authored code (kernel, Peak BIOS/UEFI, Peak drivers, scripts, and docs)
is covered by the MIT License above.

Raspberry Pi VideoCore boot firmware (`bootcode.bin`, `start*.elf`,
`fixup*.dat`, and device tree blobs) and optional Cypress/Broadcom Wi-Fi
runtime firmware are third-party binaries redistributed under the terms of
their upstream projects. Peak OS treats them as a documented binary exception:
they are fetched by `scripts/fetch-rpi-firmware.sh` into `third_party/`
(not vendored as Peak source) and may be included in flashable SD images.
See that script’s generated `LICENSE.txt` and [docs/rpi.md](docs/rpi.md).
